Class FireDangerCal

  • java.lang.Object
    • FireDangerCal

  • public class FireDangerCal
extends java.lang.Object
    ROUTINE FOR COMPUTING NATIONAL FIRE DANGER RATINGS AND FIRE LOAD INDEX DATA NEEDED FOR THE CALCULATIONS ARE: DRY, DRY BULB TEMPERATURE. WET, WET BULB TEMPERATURE. ISNOW, SOME POSITIVE NON ZERO NUMBER IF THERE IS SNOW ON THE GROUND. WIND, THE CURRENT WIND SPEED IN MILES PER HOUR. BUO, THE LAST VALUE OF THE BUILD UP INDEX. IHERB, THE CURRENT HERB STATE OF THE DISTRICT (1•CURED,2•TRANSITION, 3•GREEN DATA RETURNED ARE DF, DRYING FACTOR FFM, FINE FUEL MOISTURE, ADFM ADJUSTED (10 DAY LAG FUEL MOISTURE, GRASS SPREAD INDEX, TIMBER SPREAD INDEX. FLOAD, FIRE LOAD RATING (MAN,HOUR BASE), BUO BUILD UP INDEX
